#Chapter 1 : Commands


*Installing Git on Linux
For Fedora users: $ yum install git
For Debian-based distribution: $ sudo apt-get install git
For Others: try and visit Git website: http://git-scm.com/download/linux

*Installing on Mac
Xcode Command Line Tools
	OR
Run git from the Terminal
	OR
visit http://git-scm/download/mac
	OR
visit http://mac.github.com

*Installing on Windows
visit http://git-scm.com/download/win
	OR
visit http://windows.github.com

*Installing from Source
1.) Install the minimal dependencies for compiling and installing the Git binaries:
	$ yum install curl-devel expat-devel gettext-devel openssl-devel zlib-devel
	OR
	$ sudo apt-get install libcurl4-gnutls-dev libexpat1-dev gettext libz-dev libssl-dev
2.) Install additional dependencies (To add documentation in varous formats)
	$ yum install asciidoc xmlto docbook2x
	OR
	$ sudo apt-get install asciidoc xmlto docbook2x
3.) Get the source from  https://www.kernel.org/pub/software/scm/git OR https://github.com/git/git/releases
4.) Compile and Install:
	$ tar -zxf git-2.0.0.0.tar.gz
	$ cd git-2.0.0
	$ make configure
	$ ./configure --prefic=/usr
	$ make all doc info
	$ sudo make instal install-doc install-html instal-info
5.) To get updates:
	$ git clone git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/git/git.git



*Setting up Git
**Identity
$ git config --global user.name "gellyace"
$ git config --global user.email gelsyjuntilla@gmail.com
**Editor
$ git config --global core.editor gedit
**Checking of Settings
$ git config --list
	user.name=gellyace
	user.email=gelsyjuntilla@gmail.com
$ git config user.name
	gellyace



*Getting Help
**Get the manual page for help:
	$ git help <verb>
		OR
	$ git <verb> --help
		OR	
	$ man git-<verb>

  Example: $ git help config


	



